c=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/PeaceJam-Facebook-frame-744x74411.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"744\" height=\"744\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-3033\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Add the #Peacejam18 fb frame to your profile picture!<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">#PeaceJam18 themes:<\/h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">#Peace4All<\/h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">&amp; UN #PeaceDay #Right2Peace<\/h3>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>#PeaceJam18 connects South Sudanese and peace jammers from all over the world to increase the visibility of South Sudan online in the context of peace.<\/p>\n<p>Follow <a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">#defyhatenow<\/a> on <a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/defyhatenow11\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twitter<\/a>, like and share on <a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/defyhatenow21\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Facebook<\/a> and subscribe to our channel on <a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/videos1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Youtube.<\/a><\/p>\n<h3><b>WHAT IS A SOCIAL MEDIA #PEACEJAM?<\/b><\/h3>\n<p>A #PeaceJam is an informal gathering, event or meet-up to jam for peace online.<\/p>\n<p>Anyone can join in the social media #PeaceJam18 on Sept 21st, simply by sharing your own peace messages online. Write, speak or sing short video peace messages &#8211; or take a snapshot and upload to your favourite social media channels with the hashtags:<\/p>\n<h5>#PeaceJam18 #defyhatenow #Peace4All #Right2Peace #PeaceDay #SouthSudan<\/h5>\n<p>While you are #peacejamming, actively look for; link to; comment on and share \/ retweet any other South Sudan related peace, unity, cultural, artistic or positive development stories, organisations (grassroots, local, literacy\/education, youth, women&#8217;s, diaspora groups etc) or online peacebuilding and social media civil society \/ activism campaigns with hashtags #defyhatenow and #PeaceJam18 to help raise visibility and gain an overview of the South Sudanese peacebuilding activities and context online.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/6543482316025281\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2879 size-medium\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Peacejam2018-2-744x41911.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"744\" height=\"419\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3><b>HASHTAGS<\/b><\/h3>\n<p><i>Hashtags need to be written exactly: [#allonewordnospaces] to show up online as social media activism as this will help to trace the reach and engagement of the #PeaceJam18 messages.<\/i><\/p>\n<p>Use #PeaceJam18 &amp; #defyhatenow hashtags on all your social media posts to gain a better understanding of the social media peace landscape of South Sudan. Using #peacejam18 #defyhatenow hashtags helps track the broader South Sudanese use of online channels for positive cultural change.<\/p>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#PeaceJam18<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#defyhatenow<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#Peace4All<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#Right2Peace<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#PeaceDay<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">#SouthSudan<\/h4>\n<p><i>Include #defyhatenow &amp; #PeaceJam18 tags with every social media post, comment &amp; tweet you share!<\/i><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-871\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/dhn_04_-SS-tags-01-744x5261.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"744\" height=\"526\" \/><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>HOW TO JOIN #PEACEJAM18 ONLINE Check out the #PeaceJam18 event on Facebook. Respond by going and invite your friends to attend. Add the